Since a priori knowledge of new low-molecular PCMs in crystal phase (e.g., lattice type, space group, etc.) 
may be unavailable, it is more appropriate for DNN-O to predict the melting points of new low-molecular 
PCMs in liquid phase.

The workflow can be abstracted into four steps as follow: 
(i) Initialize the system with randomly distributed molecules
(ii) perform MD simulations with positive ∆Tm
(iii) collect the configurations generated from MD as input for DNN-O.
(iv) add the predicted ∆T_m from DNN-O on the recorded MD temperature to get the predicted melting points 
(v) average the predicted melting points for all configurations as the final result

Data preprocess pipeline:
file structure
Raw data folder
|-cry{temp}k
|         |-dump{temp}k.dump
|
|-liq{temp}k
|         |-dump{temp}k.dump
|
|-datapreprocess.py
|
|-patch_DNN_A.py
(i) Make a Dataset folder (not raw data directory!) seperately
(ii) Put data_preprocess.py under the raw data folder with dump file inside
(iii) Modify the parameter inside ({compund_name}, {phase}, {meltingpoint}, {MDtemperature} and path off folder)and run the script
(iv) if processing data of DNN_A, run patch_DNN_A.py after datapreprocess.py

After processing, there will be lots of text file in the Dataset directory:
Dataset directory
|-{compund_name}
|          |-{compund_name}_{phase}_{meltingpoint}_{MDtemperature}_{id}.txt
|          |-...
|          ...
|
|-crystal_id_list.txt
|
|-crystal_train.txt
|
|-crystal_test.txt
|
|-crystal_valid.txt
|
|-phase_id.txt

Examples can be downloaded from https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/Melting_point_MD_DATASET/30519014.

Example of prediction:
(i) Download folder MPDATASET_735816 from https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/Melting_point_MD_DATASET/30519014.
(ii) Copy the folder into paper_model folder and rename it as MPDATASET
(iii) Use the command downside

command:
cd train
python figsl.py --cfg ../yaml/DNN_O.yaml
python figsl.py --cfg ../yaml/DNN_MS.yaml
python figsl.py --cfg ../yaml/DNN_NC.yaml
python figs.py --cfg ../yaml/DNN_A.yaml

Results of the example dataset are in test folder and the result should be the same as Fig. S3.
We also provide another two example MPDATASET, named as MPDATASET_1306598 and MPDATASET_1211300

Training comand:
cd train
python train_A.py.py --cfg ../yaml/TRAIN_DNN_A.yaml
python train_MS.py.py --cfg ../yaml/TRAIN_DNN_MS.yaml
python train_O.py.py --cfg ../yaml/TRAIN_DNN_NC.yaml
python train_O.py.py --cfg ../yaml/TRAIN_DNN_O.yaml
python train_P.py.py --cfg ../yaml/TRAIN_DNN_P.yaml
python train_CP.py.py --cfg ../yaml/TRAIN_DNN_CP.yaml